President Obama spoke with Chancellor Angela Merkel of Germany to discuss the recent reports of surveillance activities allegedly conducted by the U.S. National Security Agency. The President assured the Chancellor that the United States takes the concerns of European allies seriously. They agreed to hold a high-level meeting of U.S. and German security officials to discuss these matters further. They also looked forward to initiating a U.S.-EU/EU Member State dialogue on intelligence collection and oversight, privacy, and data protection. Additionally, they expressed strong support for the launch of Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership negotiations.